<br>
Suggestion: Focus on figuring out ways that Verant can improve your pet's usability on raids rather than on any change that would improve the general stength of your pet.  <br>
<br>
Why?  Wide reaching changes aren't likely to happen until (if ever) Verant performs caster balancing.  <br>
<br>
This forum has some threads on ways to address pathing and pet usability on raids.  If you spent half as much time on those threads as on class-envy issues, they would be full of suggestions.  <br>
<br>
Once you come up with some possible solutions, unite and get Verant to listen to you.  Petitions are good, because it gets everybody lending their voice to a common message, rather than submitting a thread of a hundred different messages and opinions and rants to Verant so that they can pick out which ones they wish to address and which ones they want to igore.  <br>
<br>
Have a moratorium on emails and complaints and petitions to Verant on all other issues, and just focus on raid issues, because otherwise they'll just put everything off until the &quot;caster balancing&quot; occurs, or pick out weak posts to answer.<br>
<br>
That's it.  You aren't going to see an appreciable increase in power for levels 1-59 anytime in the near future.  It ain't how Verant works.  But you may be able to swing some changes that will benefit mages at the end-game.<br>
<br>
Because that's exactly what happened with Wizards with Bane spells.  We DID suck at raids, even with lures.  Then two Bane spells were introduced, and they revolutionised how wizards were percieved and how desired they were in guilds and on raids.  And yet they were only two spells.  But they also undoubtedly paved the way for bigger wizard nukes in Luclin.  <br>
Bone  <br>
