Why do druids have better DD spells than mages?<br>
<br>
Why did this happen from Kunark onwards?<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong, the difference between Druid and Magician DD ability is almost negligible, and probably not worth a weight in any sort of Magician balance discussion, but it is a curious fact that Druids directly and undeniably surpassed Magicians in DD ability in the post-Kunark era.<br>
<br>
They weren't far behind pre-Kunark, their twin fire/cold 612 damage nukes sneaking in behind our 600 magic dd and 810 fire bolt, but it was a distinction of sorts. <br>
<br>
I was kind of hoping someone could shed some light on why this happened <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
